  "prompt": "Why is my mobile (LeEco 1s) heating?",
  "response": "There could be several reasons why your LeEco 1s is heating up:\n\n1. Resource-intensive tasks\n- Playing graphics-heavy games\n- Running multiple apps simultaneously\n- Using GPS or navigation\n- Video streaming\n- Prolonged camera usage\n\n2. Background processes\n- Automatic app updates\n- Syncing data\n- Downloading large files\n\n3. Software issues\n- Outdated operating system\n- Malfunctioning apps\n- Memory overload\n\n4. Hardware problems\n- Battery issues\n- Processor overheating\n- Charging problems\n\n5. External factors\n- Direct sunlight exposure\n- High ambient temperature\n- Using phone while charging\n\nRecommendations:\n- Close unnecessary background apps\n- Update software\n- Avoid using phone while charging\n- Remove device case while charging\n- Check battery health\n- Restart phone periodically\n- Avoid extreme temperatures\n\nIf heating persists or becomes excessive, consider:\n- Professional device check\n- Battery replacement\n- Contacting LeEco support\n\nWarning: Persistent overheating can damage your device and potentially pose safety risks.",
